<p><b>What is a walk around on a vehicle?</b> A walk-around is a physical tour of a car that a customer has chosen, and can be a very fun part of the sales process. It's an opportunity for you to gain trust, transition from showroom to sale, and get to better know the customer and their needs.</p>
<p><b>What is the main difference between an inspection and a walk through?</b> Inspection is formal, involving detailed group scrutiny to detect defects early, while walkthrough is informal, where an author presents work to peers for feedback.</p>
<p><b>What is walk around inspection in aviation?</b> In aviation, an outside check or walk around is the air crew inspecting certain elements of an aircraft prior to boarding for security, safety, and operational reasons.</p>